<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920210-0028</DOCNO><DOCID>920210-0028.</DOCID><HL>   Financing Business:   Mark IV Industries Inc.</HL><DATE>02/10/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   IV</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)DIVERSIFIED TECHNOLOGY (DTC)STOCK AND BOND REGISTRATIONS, PRICINGS (REG)</IN><NS>BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)BOND AND STOCK REGISTRATIONS AND PRICINGS (REG)</NS><RE>NORTH AMERICA (NME)NEW YORK (NY)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   MARK IV INDUSTRIES Inc., Amherst, N.Y., said it will offer$100 million principal amount of 6 1/4% convertiblesubordinated debentures due Feb. 15, 2007. The debentures canbe converted into Mark IV common stock at the price of $24.95a share. They are being sold by Bear, Stearns andamp; Co., whichhas the option to buy as much as $14,250,000 more of theissue to cover over-allotments. Proceeds will be used torefinance debt, including $26.1 million principal amount ofMark IV's 12 3/4% subordinated debentures due Dec. 15, 2001.Mark IV previously announced it would redeem those notes onMarch 2, 1992, at a price of 104.78% of principal amount plusinterest. Mark IV makes products for audio, traffic controland other industries.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>